==English==
===Noun===
'''[[tinker]]'s [[damn]]'''
# a [[worthless]] [[amount]] (Itinerant tinkers had the reputation of being coarse and profane -- apparently peppering and punctuating their conversation with curse words to the point of extreme overuse, thereby inadvertently draining those words of their usual outlaw power.  Thus a tinker's damn had much less meaning or significance than anyone else's damn.)   
===Synonyms===
*[[tinker's cuss]]  (''mostly British'')
